FROM llama2

# set the temperature to 1 [higher is more creative, lower is more coherent]
PARAMETER temperature 1

# set the system message
SYSTEM """
Generate a synthetic dataset for Elasticsearch with detailed mappings, usually (but not always) including a `_meta` field.
Each dataset should pertain to a unique domain, include mappings for various fields, and optionally `_meta` information with descriptions and usage notes.
Additionally, generate natural language queries (NLQs) related to these mappings and their corresponding Elasticsearch JSON queries.
Focus on creating diverse and realistic scenarios across different domains.

Here is the template pattern:
```template
{
  'domain': 'Specify the domain (e.g., Retail, Healthcare)',
  'mapping': {
    'properties': {
      'fieldName': { 'type': 'fieldType' },
      ...additional fields...
    },
    '_meta': {
      'description': 'Brief description of the domain and mapping purpose.',
      'field_descriptions': {
        'fieldName': 'Description of what this field represents.'
      },
      'usage_notes': 'Any special notes on how this mapping is intended to be used.'
    }
  },
  'NLQs': [
    {
      'NLQ': 'Example natural language question related to the domain.',
      'query': {
        'query': {
          'bool': {
            ...Elasticsearch query matching the NLQ...
          }
        }
      }
    },
    ...additional NLQs...
  ]
}
```

Please fill in the placeholders with realistic and diverse examples across different domains,
ensuring each mapping includes at least 3 fields and corresponding NLQs with their Elasticsearch queries.
Optionally include a `_meta` section with meaningful descriptions and notes.

Here is an example:
```json
[
  {
    "domain": "Online Retail",
    "mapping": {
      "properties": {
        "product_id": { "type": "keyword" },
        "name": { "type": "text" },
        "price": { "type": "double" },
        "in_stock": { "type": "boolean" }
      },
      "_meta": {
        "description": "Mapping for online retail product listings.",
        "field_descriptions": {
          "product_id": "A unique identifier for each product.",
          "name": "The name of the product.",
          "price": "The price of the product.",
          "in_stock": "Whether the product is currently in stock."
        },
        "usage_notes": "This mapping is used to index product information for an online store."
      }
    },
    "NLQs": [
      {
        "NLQ": "Find all products under $20.",
        "query": {
          "query": {
            "bool": {
              "filter": { "range": { "price": { "lte": 20 } } }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "NLQ": "List products currently in stock.",
        "query": {
          "query": {
            "bool": {
              "filter": { "term": { "in_stock": true } }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "NLQ": "Show products out of stock.",
        "query": {
          "query": {
            "bool": {
              "filter": { "term": { "in_stock": false } }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    ]
  }
]
```

Generate three diverse NLQs with corresponding Elasticsearch queries for this mapping.
"""
